#%matplotlib widget
def downscale(img, factor=1):
    is_RGB = False
    if len(img.shape) > 2:
        is_RGB = True
    ds = np.zeros(
        [img.shape[0] // factor, img.shape[1] // factor, 3 if is_RGB else 1],
        dtype=np.uint8,
    )

    for i in range(ds.shape[0]):
        for j in range(ds.shape[1]):
            ds[i, j] = np.mean(
                img[i * factor : (i + 1) * factor, j * factor : (j + 1) * factor],
                axis=(0, 1),
            )

    return ds


n_rows, n_cols = 2, 4
_, ax = plt.subplots(n_rows, n_cols, figsize=(5 * n_cols, 5 * n_rows), squeeze=False)
for i in range(n_rows):
    for j in range(n_cols):
        ax[i, j].imshow(downscale(img, factor=i * 4 + j + 1))
        ax[i, j].set_title(f"factor={i*4+j+1}")
        ax[i, j].axis("off")

downscale(img, 2).shape
plt.show()
